and they shall defile thy brightness. 
\v 8 They shall bring thee down to the pit, and thou shalt die the deaths of 
\add them that are\add* slain in the midst of the seas. 
\v 9 Wilt thou yet say before him that slayeth thee, I \add am\add* God? but
thou \add shalt be\add* a man, and no God, in the hand of him that slayeth
