waters with thy feet, and fouledst their rivers. 
\v 3 Thus saith the Lord GOD; I will therefore spread out my net over thee
with a company of many people; and they shall bring thee up in my net. 
\v 4 Then will I leave thee upon the land, I will cast thee forth upon the
open field, and will cause all the fowls of the heaven to remain upon thee,
and I will fill the beasts of the whole earth with thee. 
\v 5 And I will lay thy flesh upon the mountains, and fill the valleys with
thy height. 
\v 6 I will also water with thy blood the land wherein thou swimmest, 
\add even\add* to the mountains; and the rivers shall be full of thee. 
\v 7 And when I shall put thee out, I will cover the heaven, and make the
stars thereof dark; I will cover the sun with a cloud, and the moon shall not
give her light. 
\v 8 All the bright lights of heaven will I make dark over thee, and set
darkness upon thy land, saith the Lord GOD. 
\v 9 I will also vex the hearts of many people, when I shall bring thy
destruction among the nations, into the countries which thou hast not known. 
\v 10 Yea, I will make many people amazed at thee, and their kings shall be
horribly afraid for thee, when I shall brandish my sword before them; and they
shall tremble at \add every\add* moment, every man for his own life, in the
day of thy fall.
\p
\v 11 For thus saith the Lord GOD; The sword of the king of Babylon shall come
upon thee. 
\v 12 By the swords of the mighty will I cause thy multitude to fall, the
terrible of the nations, all of them: and they shall spoil the pomp of Egypt,
and all the multitude thereof shall be destroyed. 
\v 13 I will destroy also all the beasts thereof from beside the great waters;
neither shall the foot of man trouble them any more, nor the hoofs of beasts
trouble them. 
\v 14 Then will I make their waters deep, and cause their rivers to run like
oil, saith the Lord GOD. 
\v 15 When I shall make the land of Egypt desolate, and the country shall be
destitute of that whereof it was full, when I shall smite all them that dwell
therein, then shall they know that I \add am\add* the LORD. 
\v 16 This \add is\add* the lamentation wherewith they shall lament her: the
daughters of the nations shall lament her: they shall lament for her, 
\add even\add* for Egypt, and for all her multitude, saith the Lord GOD.
\p
\v 17 It came to pass also in the twelfth year, in the fifteenth day of the
month, \add that\add* the word of the LORD came unto me, saying, 
\v 18 Son of man, wail for the multitude of Egypt, and cast them down, 
\add even\add* her, and the daughters of the famous nations, unto the nether
parts of the earth, with them that go down into the pit. 
\v 19 Whom dost thou pass in beauty? go down, and be thou laid with the
uncircumcised. 
\v 20 They shall fall in the midst of \add them that are\add* slain by the
sword: she is delivered to the sword: draw her and all her multitudes. 
\v 21 The strong among the mighty shall speak to him out of the midst of hell
with them that help him: they are gone down, they lie uncircumcised, slain by
the sword. 
\v 22 Asshur \add is\add* there and all her company: his graves \add are
\add* about him: all of them slain, fallen by the sword: 
\v 23 Whose graves are set in the sides of the pit, and her company is round
about her grave: all of them slain, fallen by the sword, which caused terror
in the land of the living. 
\v 24 There \add is\add* Elam and all her multitude round about her grave, all
of them slain, fallen by the sword, which are gone down uncircumcised into the
nether parts of the earth, which caused their terror in the land of the
living; yet have they borne their shame with them that go down to the pit. 
\v 25 They have set her a bed in the midst of the slain with all her
multitude: her graves \add are\add* round about him: all of them
uncircumcised, slain by the sword: though their terror was caused in the land
of the living, yet have they borne their shame with them that go down to the
pit: he is put in the midst of \add them that be\add* slain. 
\v 26 There \add is\add* Meshech, Tubal, and all her multitude: her graves 
\add are\add* round about him: all of them uncircumcised, slain by the sword,
though they caused their terror in the land of the living. 
\v 27 And they shall not lie with the mighty \add that are\add* fallen of the
uncircumcised, which are gone down to hell with their weapons of war: and they
have laid their swords under their heads, but their iniquities shall be upon
their bones, though \add they were\add* the terror of the mighty in the land
of the living. 
\v 28 Yea, thou shalt be broken in the midst of the uncircumcised, and shalt
lie with \add them that are\add* slain with the sword. 
\v 29 There \add is\add* Edom, her kings, and all her princes, which with
their might are laid by \add them that were\add* slain by the sword: they
shall lie with the uncircumcised, and with them that go down to the pit. 
\v 30 There \add be\add* the princes of the north, all of them, and all the
Zidonians, which are gone down with the slain; with their terror they are
ashamed of their might; and they lie uncircumcised with \add them that be
\add* slain by the sword, and bear their shame with them that go down to the
pit. 
\v 31 Pharaoh shall see them, and shall be comforted over all his multitude, 
\add even\add* Pharaoh and all his army slain by the sword, saith the Lord
GOD. 
\v 32 For I have caused my terror in the land of the living: and he shall be
laid in the midst of the uncircumcised with \add them that are\add* slain with
the sword, \add even\add* Pharaoh and all his multitude, saith the Lord GOD.
\c 33
\p
\v 1 Again the word of the LORD came unto me, saying, 
\v 2 Son of man, speak to the children of thy people, and say unto them, When
I bring the sword upon a land, if the people of the land take a man of their
coasts, and set him for their watchman: 
\v 3 If when he seeth the sword come upon the land, he blow the trumpet, and
warn the people; 
\v 4 Then whosoever heareth the sound of the trumpet, and taketh not warning;
if the sword come, and take him away, his blood shall be upon his own head. 
\v 5 He heard the sound of the trumpet, and took not warning; his blood shall
be upon him. But he that taketh warning shall deliver his soul. 
\v 6 But if the watchman see the sword come, and blow not the trumpet, and the
people be not warned; if the sword come, and take \add any\add* person from
among them, he is taken away in his iniquity; but his blood will I require at
the watchman’s hand.
\p
\v 7 So thou, O son of man, I have set thee a watchman unto the house of
Israel; therefore thou shalt hear the word at my mouth, and warn them from
me. 
\v 8 When I say unto the wicked, O wicked \add man,\add* thou shalt surely
die; if thou dost not speak to warn the wicked from his way, that wicked 
\add man\add* shall die in his iniquity; but his blood will I require at thine
hand. 
\v 9 Nevertheless, if thou warn the wicked of his way to turn from it; if he
do not turn from his way, he shall die in his iniquity; but thou hast
delivered thy soul. 
\v 10 Therefore, O thou son of man, speak unto the house of Israel; Thus ye
speak, saying, If our transgressions and our sins \add be\add* upon us, and we
pine away in them, how should we then live? 
\v 11 Say unto them, \add As\add* I live, saith the Lord GOD, I have no
pleasure in the death of the wicked; but that the wicked turn from his way and
live: turn ye, turn ye from your evil ways; for why will ye die, O house of
Israel? 
\v 12 Therefore, thou son of man, say unto the children of thy people, The
righteousness of the righteous shall not deliver him in the day of his
transgression: as for the wickedness of the wicked, he shall not fall thereby
in the day that he turneth from his wickedness; neither shall the righteous be
able to live for his \add righteousness\add* in the day that he sinneth. 
\v 13 When I shall say to the righteous, \add that\add* he shall surely live;
if he trust to his own righteousness, and commit iniquity, all his
righteousnesses shall not be remembered; but for his iniquity that he hath
committed, he shall die for it. 
\v 14 Again, when I say unto the wicked, Thou shalt surely die; if he turn
from his sin, and do that which is lawful and right; 
\v 15 \add If\add* the wicked restore the pledge, give again that he had
robbed, walk in the statutes of life, without committing iniquity; he shall
surely live, he shall not die. 
\v 16 None of his sins that he hath committed shall be mentioned unto him: he
hath done that which is lawful and right; he shall surely live.
\p
\v 17 Yet the children of thy people say, The way of the Lord is not equal:
but as for them, their way is not equal. 
\v 18 When the righteous turneth from his righteousness, and committeth
iniquity, he shall even die thereby. 
\v 19 But if the wicked turn from his wickedness, and do that which is lawful
and right, he shall live thereby.
\p
\v 20 Yet ye say, The way of the Lord is not equal. O ye house of Israel, I
will judge you every one after his ways.
\p
\v 21 And it came to pass in the twelfth year of our captivity, in the tenth 
\add month,\add* in the fifth \add day\add* of the month, \add that
\add* one that had escaped out of Jerusalem came unto me, saying, The city is
smitten. 
\v 22 Now the hand of the LORD was upon me in the evening, afore he that was
escaped came; and had opened my mouth, until he came to me in the morning; and
my mouth was opened, and I was no more dumb. 
\v 23 Then the word of the LORD came unto me, saying, 
\v 24 Son of man, they that inhabit those wastes of the land of Israel speak,
saying, Abraham was one, and he inherited the land: but we \add are
\add* many; the land is given us for inheritance. 
\v 25 Wherefore say unto them, Thus saith the Lord GOD; Ye eat with the blood,
and lift up your eyes toward your idols, and shed blood: and shall ye possess
the land? 
\v 26 Ye stand upon your sword, ye work abomination, and ye defile every one
his neighbour’s wife: and shall ye possess the land? 
\v 27 Say thou thus unto them, Thus saith the Lord GOD; \add As\add* I live,
surely they that \add are\add* in the wastes shall fall by the sword, and him
that \add is\add* in the open field will I give to the beasts to be devoured,
and they that be in the forts and in the caves shall die of the pestilence. 
\v 28 For I will lay the land most desolate, and the pomp of her strength
shall cease; and the mountains of Israel shall be desolate, that none shall
pass through. 
\v 29 Then shall they know that I \add am\add* the LORD, when I have laid the
land most desolate because of all their abominations which they have
committed.
\p
\v 30 Also, thou son of man, the children of thy people still are talking
against thee by the walls and in the doors of the houses, and speak one to
another, every one to his brother, saying, Come, I pray you, and hear what is
the word that cometh forth from the LORD. 
\v 31 And they come unto thee as the people cometh, and they sit before thee
as my people, and they hear thy words, but they will not do them: for with
their mouth they shew much love, \add but\add* their heart goeth after their
covetousness. 
\v 32 And, lo, thou \add art\add* unto them as a very lovely song of one that
hath a pleasant voice, and can play well on an instrument: for they hear thy
words, but they do them not. 
\v 33 And when this cometh to pass, (lo, it will come,) then shall they know
that a prophet hath been among them.
\c 34
\p
\v 1 And the word of the LORD came unto me, saying, 
\v 2 Son of man, prophesy against the shepherds of Israel, prophesy, and say
unto them, Thus saith the Lord GOD unto the shepherds; Woe \add be\add* to the
shepherds of Israel that do feed themselves! should not the shepherds feed the
flocks? 
\v 3 Ye eat the fat, and ye clothe you with the wool, ye kill them that are
fed: \add but\add* ye feed not the flock. 
\v 4 The diseased have ye not strengthened, neither have ye healed that which
was sick, neither have ye bound up \add that which was\add* broken, neither
have ye brought again that which was driven away, neither have ye sought that
which was lost; but with force and with cruelty have ye ruled them. 
\v 5 And they were scattered, because \add there is\add* no shepherd: and they
became meat to all the beasts of the field, when they were scattered. 
\v 6 My sheep wandered through all the mountains, and upon every high hill:
yea, my flock was scattered upon all the face of the earth, and none did
search or seek \add after them.\add*
\p
\v 7 Therefore, ye shepherds, hear the word of the LORD; 
\v 8 \add As\add* I live, saith the Lord GOD, surely because my flock became a
prey, and my flock became meat to every beast of the field, because 
\add there was\add* no shepherd, neither did my shepherds search for my flock,
but the shepherds fed themselves, and fed not my flock; 
\v 9 Therefore, O ye shepherds, hear the word of the LORD; 
\v 10 Thus saith the Lord GOD; Behold, I \add am\add* against the shepherds;
and I will require my flock at their hand, and cause them to cease from
feeding the flock; neither shall the shepherds feed themselves any more; for I
will deliver my flock from their mouth, that they may not be meat for them.
\p
\v 11 For thus saith the Lord GOD; Behold, I, \add even\add* I, will both
search my sheep, and seek them out. 
\v 12 As a shepherd seeketh out his flock in the day that he is among his
sheep \add that are\add* scattered; so will I seek out my sheep, and will
deliver them out of all places where they have been scattered in the cloudy
and dark day. 
\v 13 And I will bring them out from the people, and gather them from the
countries, and will bring them to their own land, and feed them upon the
mountains of Israel by the rivers, and in all the inhabited places of the
country. 
\v 14 I will feed them in a good pasture, and upon the high mountains of
Israel shall their fold be: there shall they lie in a good fold, and 
\add in\add* a fat pasture shall they feed upon the mountains of Israel. 
\v 15 I will feed my flock, and I will cause them to lie down, saith the Lord
GOD. 
\v 16 I will seek that which was lost, and bring again that which was driven
away, and will bind up \add that which was\add* broken, and will strengthen
that which was sick: but I will destroy the fat and the strong; I will feed
them with judgment. 
\v 17 And \add as for\add* you, O my flock, thus saith the Lord GOD; Behold, I
judge between cattle and cattle, between the rams and the he goats. 
\v 18 \add Seemeth it\add* a small thing unto you to have eaten up the good
pasture, but ye must tread down with your feet the residue of your pastures?
and to have drunk of the deep waters, but ye must foul the residue with your
feet? 
\v 19 And \add as for\add* my flock, they eat that which ye have trodden with
your feet; and they drink that which ye have fouled with your feet.
\p
\v 20 Therefore thus saith the Lord GOD unto them; Behold, I, \add even
\add* I, will judge between the fat cattle and between the lean cattle. 
\v 21 Because ye have thrust with side and with shoulder, and pushed all the
diseased with your horns, till ye have scattered them abroad; 
\v 22 Therefore will I save my flock, and they shall no more be a prey; and I
will judge between cattle and cattle. 
\v 23 And I will set up one shepherd over them, and he shall feed them, 
\add even\add* my servant David; he shall feed them, and he shall be their
shepherd. 
\v 24 And I the LORD will be their God, and my servant David a prince among
them; I the LORD have spoken \add it. \add*
\v 25 And I will make with them a covenant of peace, and will cause the evil
beasts to cease out of the land: and they shall dwell safely in the
wilderness, and sleep in the woods. 
\v 26 And I will make them and the places round about my hill a blessing; and
I will cause the shower to come down in his season; there shall be showers of
blessing. 
\v 27 And the tree of the field shall yield her fruit, and the earth shall
yield her increase, and they shall be safe in their land, and shall know that
I \add am\add* the LORD, when I have broken the bands of their yoke, and
delivered them out of the hand of those that served themselves of them. 
\v 28 And they shall no more be a prey to the heathen, neither shall the beast
of the land devour them; but they shall dwell safely, and none shall make 
\add them\add* afraid. 
\v 29 And I will raise up for them a plant of renown, and they shall be no
more consumed with hunger in the land, neither bear the shame of the heathen
any more. 
\v 30 Thus shall they know that I the LORD their God \add am\add* with them,
and \add that\add* they, \add even\add* the house of Israel, \add are
\add* my people, saith the Lord GOD. 
\v 31 And ye my flock, the flock of my pasture, \add are\add* men, \add and
\add* I \add am\add* your God, saith the Lord GOD.
\c 35
\p
\v 1 Moreover the word of the LORD came unto me, saying, 
\v 2 Son of man, set thy face against mount Seir, and prophesy against it, 
\v 3 And say unto it, Thus saith the Lord GOD; Behold, O mount Seir, I 
\add am\add* against thee, and I will stretch out mine hand against thee, and
I will make thee most desolate. 
\v 4 I will lay thy cities waste, and thou shalt be desolate, and thou shalt
know that I \add am\add* the LORD. 
\v 5 Because thou hast had a perpetual hatred, and hast shed \add the blood
of\add* the children of Israel by the force of the sword in the time of their
calamity, in the time \add that their\add* iniquity \add had\add* an end: 
\v 6 Therefore, \add as\add* I live, saith the Lord GOD, I will prepare thee
unto blood, and blood shall pursue thee: sith thou hast not hated blood, even
blood shall pursue thee. 
\v 7 Thus will I make mount Seir most desolate, and cut off from it him that
passeth out and him that returneth. 
\v 8 And I will fill his mountains with his slain \add men:\add* in thy hills,
and in thy valleys, and in all thy rivers, shall they fall that are slain with
the sword. 
\v 9 I will make thee perpetual desolations, and thy cities shall not return:
and ye shall know that I \add am\add* the LORD. 
\v 10 Because thou hast said, These two nations and these two countries shall
be mine, and we will possess it; whereas the LORD was there: 
\v 11 Therefore, as I live, saith the Lord GOD, I will even do according to
thine anger, and according to thine envy which thou hast used out of thy
hatred against them; and I will make myself known among them, when I have
judged thee. 
\v 12 And thou shalt know that I \add am\add* the LORD, \add and that
\add* I have heard all thy blasphemies which thou hast spoken against the
mountains of Israel, saying, They are laid desolate, they are given us to
consume. 
\v 13 Thus with your mouth ye have boasted against me, and have multiplied
your words against me: I have heard \add them. \add*
\v 14 Thus saith the Lord GOD; When the whole earth rejoiceth, I will make
thee desolate. 
\v 15 As thou didst rejoice at the inheritance of the house of Israel, because
it was desolate, so will I do unto thee: thou shalt be desolate, O mount Seir,
and all Idumea, \add even\add* all of it: and they shall know that I 
\add am\add* the LORD.
\c 36
\p
\v 1 Also, thou son of man, prophesy unto the mountains of Israel, and say, Ye
mountains of Israel, hear the word of the LORD: 
\v 2 Thus saith the Lord GOD; Because the enemy hath said against you, Aha,
even the ancient high places are ours in possession: 
\v 3 Therefore prophesy and say, Thus saith the Lord GOD; Because they have
made \add you\add* desolate, and swallowed you up on every side, that ye might
be a possession unto the residue of the heathen, and ye are taken up in the
lips of talkers, and \add are\add* an infamy of the people: 
\v 4 Therefore, ye mountains of Israel, hear the word of the Lord GOD; Thus
saith the Lord GOD to the mountains, and to the hills, to the rivers, and to
the valleys, to the desolate wastes, and to the cities that are forsaken,
which became a prey and derision to the residue of the heathen that 
\add are\add* round about; 
\v 5 Therefore thus saith the Lord GOD; Surely in the fire of my jealousy have
I spoken against the residue of the heathen, and against all Idumea, which
have appointed my land into their possession with the joy of all \add their
\add* heart, with despiteful minds, to cast it out for a prey. 
\v 6 Prophesy therefore concerning the land of Israel, and say unto the
mountains, and to the hills, to the rivers, and to the valleys, Thus saith the
Lord GOD; Behold, I have spoken in my jealousy and in my fury, because ye have
borne the shame of the heathen: 
\v 7 Therefore thus saith the Lord GOD; I have lifted up mine hand, Surely the
heathen that \add are\add* about you, they shall bear their shame.
\p
\v 8 But ye, O mountains of Israel, ye shall shoot forth your branches, and
yield your fruit to my people of Israel; for they are at hand to come. 
\v 9 For, behold, I \add am\add* for you, and I will turn unto you, and ye
shall be tilled and sown: 
\v 10 And I will multiply men upon you, all the house of Israel, \add even
\add* all of it: and the cities shall be inhabited, and the wastes shall be
builded: 
\v 11 And I will multiply upon you man and beast; and they shall increase and
bring fruit: and I will settle you after your old estates, and will do better
\add unto you\add* than at your beginnings: and ye shall know that I 
\add am\add* the LORD. 
\v 12 Yea, I will cause men to walk upon you, \add even\add* my people Israel;
and they shall possess thee, and thou shalt be their inheritance, and thou
shalt no more henceforth bereave them \add of men. \add*
\v 13 Thus saith the Lord GOD; Because they say unto you, Thou \add land
\add* devourest up men, and hast bereaved thy nations; 
\v 14 Therefore thou shalt devour men no more, neither bereave thy nations any
more, saith the Lord GOD. 
\v 15 Neither will I cause \add men\add* to hear in thee the shame of the
heathen any more, neither shalt thou bear the reproach of the people any more,
neither shalt thou cause thy nations to fall any more, saith the Lord GOD.
\p
\v 16 Moreover the word of the LORD came unto me, saying, 
\v 17 Son of man, when the house of Israel dwelt in their own land, they
defiled it by their own way and by their doings: their way was before me as
the uncleanness of a removed woman. 
\v 18 Wherefore I poured my fury upon them for the blood that they had shed
upon the land, and for their idols \add wherewith\add* they had polluted it: 
\v 19 And I scattered them among the heathen, and they were dispersed through
the countries: according to their way and according to their doings I judged
them. 
\v 20 And when they entered unto the heathen, whither they went, they profaned
my holy name, when they said to them, These \add are\add* the people of the
LORD, and are gone forth out of his land.
\p
\v 21 But I had pity for mine holy name, which the house of Israel had
profaned among the heathen, whither they went. 
\v 22 Therefore say unto the house of Israel, Thus saith the Lord GOD; I do
not \add this\add* for your sakes, O house of Israel, but for mine holy name’s
sake, which ye have profaned among the heathen, whither ye went. 
\v 23 And I will sanctify my great name, which was profaned among the heathen,
which ye have profaned in the midst of them; and the heathen shall know that I
\add am\add* the LORD, saith the Lord GOD, when I shall be sanctified in you
before their eyes. 
\v 24 For I will take you from among the heathen, and gather you out of all
countries, and will bring you into your own land.
\p
\v 25 Then will I sprinkle clean water upon you, and ye shall be clean: from
all your filthiness, and from all your idols, will I cleanse you. 
\v 26 A new heart also will I give you, and a new spirit will I put within
you: and I will take away the stony heart out of your flesh, and I will give
you an heart of flesh. 
\v 27 And I will put my spirit within you, and cause you to walk in my
statutes, and ye shall keep my judgments, and do \add them. \add*
\v 28 And ye shall dwell in the land that I gave to your fathers; and ye shall
be my people, and I will be your God. 
\v 29 I will also save you from all your uncleannesses: and I will call for
the corn, and will increase it, and lay no famine upon you. 
\v 30 And I will multiply the fruit of the tree, and the increase of the
field, that ye shall receive no more reproach of famine among the heathen. 
\v 31 Then shall ye remember your own evil ways, and your doings that 
\add were\add* not good, and shall lothe yourselves in your own sight for your
iniquities and for your abominations. 
\v 32 Not for your sakes do I \add this,\add* saith the Lord GOD, be it known
unto you: be ashamed and confounded for your own ways, O house of Israel. 
\v 33 Thus saith the Lord GOD; In the day that I shall have cleansed you from
all your iniquities I will also cause \add you\add* to dwell in the cities,
and the wastes shall be builded. 
\v 34 And the desolate land shall be tilled, whereas it lay desolate in the
sight of all that passed by. 
\v 35 And they shall say, This land that was desolate is become like the
garden of Eden; and the waste and desolate and ruined cities \add are become
\add* fenced, \add and\add* are inhabited. 
\v 36 Then the heathen that are left round about you shall know that I the
LORD build the ruined \add places, and\add* plant that that was desolate: I
the LORD have spoken \add it,\add* and I will do \add it. \add*
\v 37 Thus saith the Lord GOD; I will yet \add for\add* this be enquired of by
the house of Israel, to do \add it\add* for them; I will increase them with
men like a flock. 
\v 38 As the holy flock, as the flock of Jerusalem in her solemn feasts; so
shall the waste cities be filled with flocks of men: and they shall know that
I \add am\add* the LORD.
\c 37
\p
\v 1 The hand of the LORD was upon me, and carried me out in the spirit of the
LORD, and set me down in the midst of the valley which \add was\add* full of
bones, 
\v 2 And caused me to pass by them round about: and, behold, \add there were
\add* very many in the open valley; and, lo, \add they were\add* very dry. 
\v 3 And he said unto me, Son of man, can these bones live? And I answered, O
Lord GOD, thou knowest. 
\v 4 Again he said unto me, Prophesy upon these bones, and say unto them, O ye
dry bones, hear the word of the LORD. 
\v 5 Thus saith the Lord GOD unto these bones; Behold, I will cause breath to
enter into you, and ye shall live: 
\v 6 And I will lay sinews upon you, and will bring up flesh upon you, and
cover you with skin, and put breath in you, and ye shall live; and ye shall
know that I \add am\add* the LORD. 
\v 7 So I prophesied as I was commanded: and as I prophesied, there was a
noise, and behold a shaking, and the bones came together, bone to his bone. 
\v 8 And when I beheld, lo, the sinews and the flesh came up upon them, and
the skin covered them above: but \add there was \add*no breath in them. 
\v 9 Then said he unto me, Prophesy unto the wind, prophesy, son of man, and
say to the wind, Thus saith the Lord GOD; Come from the four winds, O breath,
and breathe upon these slain, that they may live. 
\v 10 So I prophesied as he commanded me, and the breath came into them, and
they lived, and stood up upon their feet, an exceeding great army.
\p
\v 11 Then he said unto me, Son of man, these bones are the whole house of
Israel: behold, they say, Our bones are dried, and our hope is lost: we are
cut off for our parts. 
\v 12 Therefore prophesy and say unto them, Thus saith the Lord GOD; Behold, O
my people, I will open your graves, and cause you to come up out of your
graves, and bring you into the land of Israel. 
\v 13 And ye shall know that I \add am\add* the LORD, when I have opened your
graves, O my people, and brought you up out of your graves, 
\v 14 And shall put my spirit in you, and ye shall live, and I shall place you
in your own land: then shall ye know that I the LORD have spoken \add it,
\add* and performed \add it,\add* saith the LORD.
\p
\v 15 The word of the LORD came again unto me, saying, 
\v 16 Moreover, thou son of man, take thee one stick, and write upon it, For
Judah, and for the children of Israel his companions: then take another stick,
and write upon it, For Joseph, the stick of Ephraim, and \add for\add* all the
house of Israel his companions: 
\v 17 And join them one to another into one stick; and they shall become one
in thine hand.
\p
\v 18 And when the children of thy people shall speak unto thee, saying, Wilt
thou not shew us what thou \add meanest\add* by these? 
\v 19 Say unto them, Thus saith the Lord GOD; Behold, I will take the stick of
Joseph, which \add is\add* in the hand of Ephraim, and the tribes of Israel
his fellows, and will put them with him, \add even\add* with the stick of
Judah, and make them one stick, and they shall be one in mine hand.
\p
\v 20 And the sticks whereon thou writest shall be in thine hand before their
eyes. 
\v 21 And say unto them, Thus saith the Lord GOD; Behold, I will take the
children of Israel from among the heathen, whither they be gone, and will
gather them on every side, and bring them into their own land: 
\v 22 And I will make them one nation in the land upon the mountains of
Israel; and one king shall be king to them all: and they shall be no more two
nations, neither shall they be divided into two kingdoms any more at all: 
\v 23 Neither shall they defile themselves any more with their idols, nor with
their detestable things, nor with any of their transgressions: but I will save
them out of all their dwellingplaces, wherein they have sinned, and will
cleanse them: so shall they be my people, and I will be their God. 
\v 24 And David my servant \add shall be\add* king over them; and they all
shall have one shepherd: they shall also walk in my judgments, and observe my
statutes, and do them. 
\v 25 And they shall dwell in the land that I have given unto Jacob my
servant, wherein your fathers have dwelt; and they shall dwell therein, 
\add even\add* they, and their children, and their children’s children for
ever: and my servant David \add shall be\add* their prince for ever. 
\v 26 Moreover I will make a covenant of peace with them; it shall be an
everlasting covenant with them: and I will place them, and multiply them, and
will set my sanctuary in the midst of them for evermore. 
\v 27 My tabernacle also shall be with them: yea, I will be their God, and
they shall be my people. 
\v 28 And the heathen shall know that I the LORD do sanctify Israel, when my
sanctuary shall be in the midst of them for evermore.
\c 38
\p
\v 1 And the word of the LORD came unto me, saying, 
\v 2 Son of man, set thy face against Gog, the land of Magog, the chief prince
of Meshech and Tubal, and prophesy against him, 
\v 3 And say, Thus saith the Lord GOD; Behold I \add am\add* against thee, O
Gog, the chief prince of Meshech and Tubal: 
\v 4 And I will turn thee back, and put hooks into thy jaws, and I will bring
thee forth, and all thine army, horses and horsemen, all of them clothed with
all sorts \add of armour, even\add* a great company \add with\add* bucklers
and shields, all of them handling swords: 
\v 5 Persia, Ethiopia, and Libya with them; all of them with shield and
helmet: 
\v 6 Gomer, and all his bands; the house of Togarmah of the north quarters,
and all his bands: \add and\add* many people with thee. 
\v 7 Be thou prepared, and prepare for thyself, thou, and all thy company that
are assembled unto thee, and be thou a guard unto them.
\p
\v 8 After many days thou shalt be visited: in the latter years thou shalt
come into the land \add that is\add* brought back from the sword, \add and is
\add* gathered out of many people, against the mountains of Israel, which have
been always waste: but it is brought forth out of the nations, and they shall
dwell safely all of them. 
\v 9 Thou shalt ascend and come like a storm, thou shalt be like a cloud to
cover the land, thou, and all thy bands, and many people with thee. 
\v 10 Thus saith the Lord GOD; It shall also come to pass, \add that
\add* at the same time shall things come into thy mind, and thou shalt think
an evil thought: 
\v 11 And thou shalt say, I will go up to the land of unwalled villages; I
will go to them that are at rest, that dwell safely, all of them dwelling
without walls, and having neither bars nor gates, 
\v 12 To take a spoil, and to take a prey; to turn thine hand upon the
desolate places \add that are now\add* inhabited, and upon the people 
\add that are\add* gathered out of the nations, which have gotten cattle and
goods, that dwell in the midst of the land. 
\v 13 Sheba, and Dedan, and the merchants of Tarshish, with all the young
lions thereof, shall say unto thee, Art thou come to take a spoil? hast thou
gathered thy company to take a prey? to carry away silver and gold, to take
away cattle and goods, to take a great spoil?
\p
\v 14 Therefore, son of man, prophesy and say unto Gog, Thus saith the Lord
GOD; In that day when my people of Israel dwelleth safely, shalt thou not know
\add it? \add*
\v 15 And thou shalt come from thy place out of the north parts, thou, and
many people with thee, all of them riding upon horses, a great company, and a
mighty army: 
\v 16 And thou shalt come up against my people of Israel, as a cloud to cover
the land; it shall be in the latter days, and I will bring thee against my
land, that the heathen may know me, when I shall be sanctified in thee, O Gog,
before their eyes. 
\v 17 Thus saith the Lord GOD; \add Art\add* thou he of whom I have spoken in
old time by my servants the prophets of Israel, which prophesied in those days
\add many\add* years that I would bring thee against them? 
\v 18 And it shall come to pass at the same time when Gog shall come against
the land of Israel, saith the Lord GOD, \add that\add* my fury shall come up
in my face. 
\v 19 For in my jealousy \add and\add* in the fire of my wrath have I spoken,
Surely in that day there shall be a great shaking in the land of Israel; 
\v 20 So that the fishes of the sea, and the fowls of the heaven, and the
beasts of the field, and all creeping things that creep upon the earth, and
all the men that \add are\add* upon the face of the earth, shall shake at my
presence, and the mountains shall be thrown down, and the steep places shall
fall, and every wall shall fall to the ground. 
\v 21 And I will call for a sword against him throughout all my mountains,
saith the Lord GOD: every man’s sword shall be against his brother. 
\v 22 And I will plead against him with pestilence and with blood; and I will
rain upon him, and upon his bands, and upon the many people that \add are
\add* with him, an overflowing rain, and great hailstones, fire, and
brimstone. 
\v 23 Thus will I magnify myself, and sanctify myself; and I will be known in
the eyes of many nations, and they shall know that I \add am\add* the LORD.
\c 39
\p
\v 1 Therefore, thou son of man, prophesy against Gog, and say, Thus saith the
Lord GOD; Behold, I \add am\add* against thee, O Gog, the chief prince of
Meshech and Tubal: 
\v 2 And I will turn thee back, and leave but the sixth part of thee, and will
cause thee to come up from the north parts, and will bring thee upon the
mountains of Israel: 
\v 3 And I will smite thy bow out of thy left hand, and will cause thine
arrows to fall out of thy right hand. 
\v 4 Thou shalt fall upon the mountains of Israel, thou, and all thy bands,
and the people that \add is\add* with thee: I will give thee unto the ravenous
birds of every sort, and \add to\add* the beasts of the field to be devoured.
\v 5 Thou shalt fall upon the open field: for I have spoken \add it,
\add* saith the Lord GOD. 
\v 6 And I will send a fire on Magog, and among them that dwell carelessly in
the isles: and they shall know that I \add am\add* the LORD. 
\v 7 So will I make my holy name known in the midst of my people Israel; and I
will not \add let them\add* pollute my holy name any more: and the heathen
shall know that I \add am\add* the LORD, the Holy One in Israel.
\p
\v 8 Behold, it is come, and it is done, saith the Lord GOD; this \add is
\add* the day whereof I have spoken. 
\v 9 And they that dwell in the cities of Israel shall go forth, and shall set
on fire and burn the weapons, both the shields and the bucklers, the bows and
the arrows, and the handstaves, and the spears, and they shall burn them with
fire seven years: 
\v 10 So that they shall take no wood out of the field, neither cut down 
\add any\add* out of the forests; for they shall burn the weapons with fire:
and they shall spoil those that spoiled them, and rob those that robbed them,
saith the Lord GOD.
\p
\v 11 And it shall come to pass in that day, \add that\add* I will give unto
Gog a place there of graves in Israel, the valley of the passengers on the
east of the sea: and it shall stop the \add noses\add* of the passengers: and
there shall they bury Gog and all his multitude: and they shall call 
\add it\add* The valley of Hamon-gog. 
\v 12 And seven months shall the house of Israel be burying of them, that they
may cleanse the land. 
\v 13 Yea, all the people of the land shall bury \add them;\add* and it shall
be to them a renown the day that I shall be glorified, saith the Lord GOD. 
\v 14 And they shall sever out men of continual employment, passing through
the land to bury with the passengers those that remain upon the face of the
earth, to cleanse it: after the end of seven months shall they search. 
\v 15 And the passengers \add that\add* pass through the land, when 
\add any\add* seeth a man’s bone, then shall he set up a sign by it, till the
buriers have buried it in the valley of Hamon-gog. 
\v 16 And also the name of the city \add shall be\add* Hamonah. Thus shall
they cleanse the land.
\p
\v 17 And, thou son of man, thus saith the Lord GOD; Speak unto every
feathered fowl, and to every beast of the field, Assemble yourselves, and
come; gather yourselves on every side to my sacrifice that I do sacrifice for
you, \add even\add* a great sacrifice upon the mountains of Israel, that ye
may eat flesh, and drink blood. 
\v 18 Ye shall eat the flesh of the mighty, and drink the blood of the princes
of the earth, of rams, of lambs, and of goats, of bullocks, all of them
fatlings of Bashan. 
\v 19 And ye shall eat fat till ye be full, and drink blood till ye be
drunken, of my sacrifice which I have sacrificed for you. 
\v 20 Thus ye shall be filled at my table with horses and chariots, with
mighty men, and with all men of war, saith the Lord GOD. 
\v 21 And I will set my glory among the heathen, and all the heathen shall see
my judgment that I have executed, and my hand that I have laid upon them. 
\v 22 So the house of Israel shall know that I \add am\add* the LORD their God
from that day and forward.
\p
\v 23 And the heathen shall know that the house of Israel went into captivity
for their iniquity: because they trespassed against me, therefore hid I my
face from them, and gave them into the hand of their enemies: so fell they all
by the sword. 
\v 24 According to their uncleanness and according to their transgressions
have I done unto them, and hid my face from them. 
\v 25 Therefore thus saith the Lord GOD; Now will I bring again the captivity
of Jacob, and have mercy upon the whole house of Israel, and will be jealous
for my holy name; 
\v 26 After that they have borne their shame, and all their trespasses whereby
they have trespassed against me, when they dwelt safely in their land, and
none made \add them\add* afraid. 
\v 27 When I have brought them again from the people, and gathered them out of
their enemies’ lands, and am sanctified in them in the sight of many nations;
\v 28 Then shall they know that I \add am\add* the LORD their God, which
caused them to be led into captivity among the heathen: but I have gathered
them unto their own land, and have left none of them any more there. 
\v 29 Neither will I hide my face any more from them: for I have poured out my
spirit upon the house of Israel, saith the Lord GOD.
\c 40
\p
\v 1 In the five and twentieth year of our captivity, in the beginning of the
year, in the tenth \add day\add* of the month, in the fourteenth year after
that the city was smitten, in the selfsame day the hand of the LORD was upon
me, and brought me thither. 
\v 2 In the visions of God brought he me into the land of Israel, and set me
upon a very high mountain, by which \add was\add* as the frame of a city on
the south. 
\v 3 And he brought me thither, and, behold, \add there was\add* a man, whose
appearance was like the appearance of brass, with a line of flax in his hand,
and a measuring reed; and he stood in the gate. 
\v 4 And the man said unto me, Son of man, behold with thine eyes, and hear
with thine ears, and set thine heart upon all that I shall shew thee; for to
the intent that I might shew \add them\add* unto thee \add art\add* thou
brought hither: declare all that thou seest to the house of Israel. 
\v 5 And behold a wall on the outside of the house round about, and in the
man’s hand a measuring reed of six cubits \add long\add* by the cubit and an
hand breadth: so he measured the breadth of the building, one reed; and the
height, one reed.
\p
\v 6 Then came he unto the gate which looketh toward the east, and went up the
stairs thereof, and measured the threshold of the gate, \add which was
\add* one reed broad; and the other threshold \add of the gate, which was
\add* one reed broad. 
\v 7 And \add every\add* little chamber \add was\add* one reed long, and one
reed broad; and between the little chambers \add were\add* five cubits; and
the threshold of the gate by the porch of the gate within \add was\add* one
reed. 
\v 8 He measured also the porch of the gate within, one reed. 
\v 9 Then measured he the porch of the gate, eight cubits; and the posts
thereof, two cubits; and the porch of the gate \add was\add* inward. 
\v 10 And the little chambers of the gate eastward \add were\add* three on
this side, and three on that side; they three \add were\add* of one measure:
and the posts had one measure on this side and on that side. 
\v 11 And he measured the breadth of the entry of the gate, ten cubits; 
\add and\add* the length of the gate, thirteen cubits. 
\v 12 The space also before the little chambers \add was\add* one cubit 
\add on this side,\add* and the space \add was\add* one cubit on that side:
and the little chambers \add were\add* six cubits on this side, and six cubits
on that side. 
\v 13 He measured then the gate from the roof of \add one\add* little chamber
to the roof of another: the breadth \add was\add* five and twenty cubits, door
against door. 
\v 14 He made also posts of threescore cubits, even unto the post of the court
round about the gate. 
\v 15 And from the face of the gate of the entrance unto the face of the porch
of the inner gate \add were\add* fifty cubits. 
\v 16 And \add there were\add* narrow windows to the little chambers, and to
their posts within the gate round about, and likewise to the arches: and
windows \add were\add* round about inward: and upon \add each\add* post 
\add were\add* palm trees. 
\v 17 Then brought he me into the outward court, and, lo, \add there were
\add* chambers, and a pavement made for the court round about: thirty chambers
\add were\add* upon the pavement. 
\v 18 And the pavement by the side of the gates over against the length of the
gates \add was\add* the lower pavement. 
\v 19 Then he measured the breadth from the forefront of the lower gate unto
the forefront of the inner court without, an hundred cubits eastward and
northward.
\p
\v 20 And the gate of the outward court that looked toward the north, he
measured the length thereof, and the breadth thereof. 
\v 21 And the little chambers thereof \add were\add* three on this side and
three on that side; and the posts thereof and the arches thereof were after
the measure of the first gate: the length thereof \add was\add* fifty cubits,
and the breadth five and twenty cubits. 
\v 22 And their windows, and their arches, and their palm trees, \add were
\add* after the measure of the gate that looketh toward the east; and they
went up unto it by seven steps; and the arches thereof \add were\add* before
them. 
\v 23 And the gate of the inner court \add was\add* over against the gate
toward the north, and toward the east; and he measured from gate to gate an
hundred cubits.
\p
\v 24 After that he brought me toward the south, and behold a gate toward the
south: and he measured the posts thereof and the arches thereof according to
these measures. 
\v 25 And \add there were\add* windows in it and in the arches thereof round
about, like those windows: the length \add was\add* fifty cubits, and the
breadth five and twenty cubits. 
\v 26 And \add there were\add* seven steps to go up to it, and the arches
thereof \add were\add* before them: and it had palm trees, one on this side,
and another on that side, upon the posts thereof. 
\v 27 And \add there was\add* a gate in the inner court toward the south: and
he measured from gate to gate toward the south an hundred cubits. 
\v 28 And he brought me to the inner court by the south gate: and he measured
the south gate according to these measures; 
\v 29 And the little chambers thereof, and the posts thereof, and the arches
thereof, according to these measures: and \add there were\add* windows in it
and in the arches thereof round about: \add it was\add* fifty cubits long, and
five and twenty cubits broad. 
\v 30 And the arches round about \add were\add* five and twenty cubits long,
and five cubits broad. 
\v 31 And the arches thereof \add were\add* toward the utter court; and palm
trees \add were\add* upon the posts thereof: and the going up to it 
\add had\add* eight steps.
\p
\v 32 And he brought me into the inner court toward the east: and he measured
the gate according to these measures. 
\v 33 And the little chambers thereof, and the posts thereof, and the arches
thereof, \add were\add* according to these measures: and \add there were
\add* windows therein and in the arches thereof round about: \add it was
\add* fifty cubits long, and five and twenty cubits broad. 
\v 34 And the arches thereof \add were\add* toward the outward court; and palm
trees \add were\add* upon the posts thereof, on this side, and on that side:
and the going up to it \add had\add* eight steps. 
\v 35 And he brought me to the north gate, and measured \add it\add* according
to these measures; 
\v 36 The little chambers thereof, the posts thereof, and the arches thereof,
and the windows to it round about: the length \add was\add* fifty cubits, and
the breadth five and twenty cubits. 
\v 37 And the posts thereof \add were\add* toward the utter court; and palm
trees \add were\add* upon the posts thereof, on this side, and on that side:
and the going up to it \add had\add* eight steps. 
\v 38 And the chambers and the entries thereof \add were\add* by the posts of
the gates, where they washed the burnt offering.
\p
\v 39 And in the porch of the gate \add were\add* two tables on this side, and
two tables on that side, to slay thereon the burnt offering and the sin
offering and the trespass offering. 
\v 40 And at the side without, as one goeth up to the entry of the north gate,
\add were\add* two tables; and on the other side, which \add was\add* at the
porch of the gate, \add were\add* two tables. 
\v 41 Four tables \add were\add* on this side, and four tables on that side,
by the side of the gate; eight tables, whereupon they slew \add their
sacrifices. \add*
\v 42 And the four tables \add were\add* of hewn stone for the burnt offering,
of a cubit and an half long, and a cubit and an half broad, and one cubit
