\v 43 And within \add were\add* hooks, an hand broad, fastened round about:
and upon the tables \add was\add* the flesh of the offering.
\p
\v 44 And without the inner gate \add were\add* the chambers of the singers in
the inner court, which \add was\add* at the side of the north gate; and their
prospect \add was\add* toward the south: one at the side of the east gate 
\add having\add* the prospect toward the north. 
\v 45 And he said unto me, This chamber, whose prospect \add is\add* toward
the south, \add is\add* for the priests, the keepers of the charge of the
house. 
\v 46 And the chamber whose prospect \add is\add* toward the north \add is
\add* for the priests, the keepers of the charge of the altar: these 
\add are\add* the sons of Zadok among the sons of Levi, which come near to the
LORD to minister unto him. 
\v 47 So he measured the court, an hundred cubits long, and an hundred cubits
broad, foursquare; and the altar \add that was\add* before the house.
\p
\v 48 And he brought me to the porch of the house, and measured \add each
\add* post of the porch, five cubits on this side, and five cubits on that
side: and the breadth of the gate \add was\add* three cubits on this side, and
three cubits on that side. 
\v 49 The length of the porch \add was\add* twenty cubits, and the breadth
eleven cubits; and \add he brought me\add* by the steps whereby they went up
to it: and \add there were\add* pillars by the posts, one on this side, and
another on that side.
\c 41
\p
\v 1 Afterward he brought me to the temple, and measured the posts, six cubits
broad on the one side, and six cubits broad on the other side, \add which was
\add* the breadth of the tabernacle. 
\v 2 And the breadth of the door \add was\add* ten cubits; and the sides of
the door \add were\add* five cubits on the one side, and five cubits on the
