hold in the wall of the house. 
\v 7 And \add there was\add* an enlarging, and a winding about still upward to
the side chambers: for the winding about of the house went still upward round
about the house: therefore the breadth of the house \add was still\add*
upward, and so increased \add from\add* the lowest \add chamber\add* to the
highest by the midst. 
\v 8 I saw also the height of the house round about: the foundations of the
side chambers \add were\add* a full reed of six great cubits. 
\v 9 The thickness of the wall, which \add was\add* for the side chamber
without, \add was\add* five cubits: and \add that\add* which \add was
\add* left \add was\add* the place of the side chambers that \add were
\add* within. 
\v 10 And between the chambers \add was\add* the wideness of twenty cubits
round about the house on every side. 
\v 11 And the doors of the side chambers \add were\add* toward \add the place
that was\add* left, one door toward the north, and another door toward the
south: and the breadth of the place that was left \add was\add* five cubits
round about. 
\v 12 Now the building that \add was\add* before the separate place at the end
