\add* the table that \add is\add* before the LORD. 
\v 23 And the temple and the sanctuary had two doors. 
\v 24 And the doors had two leaves \add apiece,\add* two turning leaves; two 
\add leaves\add* for the one door, and two leaves for the other \add door. 
\add*
\v 25 And \add there were\add* made on them, on the doors of the temple,
cherubims and palm trees, like as \add were\add* made upon the walls; and 
\add there were\add* thick planks upon the face of the porch without. 
\v 26 And \add there were\add* narrow windows and palm trees on the one side
and on the other side, on the sides of the porch, and \add upon\add* the side
chambers of the house, and thick planks.
\c 42
\p
\v 1 Then he brought me forth into the utter court, the way toward the north:
and he brought me into the chamber that \add was\add* over against the
separate place, and which \add was\add* before the building toward the north.
\v 2 Before the length of an hundred cubits \add was\add* the north door, and
