\v 3 Over against the twenty \add cubits\add* which \add were\add* for the
inner court, and over against the pavement which \add was\add* for the utter
court, \add was\add* gallery against gallery in three \add stories. 
\add*
\v 4 And before the chambers \add was\add* a walk of ten cubits breadth
inward, a way of one cubit; and their doors toward the north. 
\v 5 Now the upper chambers \add were\add* shorter: for the galleries were
