\c 44
\p
\v 1 Then he brought me back the way of the gate of the outward sanctuary
which looketh toward the east; and it \add was\add* shut. 
\v 2 Then said the LORD unto me; This gate shall be shut, it shall not be
opened, and no man shall enter in by it; because the LORD, the God of Israel,
hath entered in by it, therefore it shall be shut. 
\v 3 \add It is\add* for the prince; the prince, he shall sit in it to eat
bread before the LORD; he shall enter by the way of the porch of \add that
\add* gate, and shall go out by the way of the same.
\p
\v 4 Then brought he me the way of the north gate before the house: and I
looked, and, behold, the glory of the LORD filled the house of the LORD: and I
fell upon my face. 
\v 5 And the LORD said unto me, Son of man, mark well, and behold with thine
eyes, and hear with thine ears all that I say unto thee concerning all the
ordinances of the house of the LORD, and all the laws thereof; and mark well
the entering in of the house, with every going forth of the sanctuary. 
\v 6 And thou shalt say to the rebellious, \add even\add* to the house of
Israel, Thus saith the Lord GOD; O ye house of Israel, let it suffice you of
all your abominations, 
\v 7 In that ye have brought \add into my sanctuary\add* strangers,
uncircumcised in heart, and uncircumcised in flesh, to be in my sanctuary, to
pollute it, \add even\add* my house, when ye offer my bread, the fat and the
