\v 8 And ye have not kept the charge of mine holy things: but ye have set
keepers of my charge in my sanctuary for yourselves.
\p
\v 9 Thus saith the Lord GOD; No stranger, uncircumcised in heart, nor
uncircumcised in flesh, shall enter into my sanctuary, of any stranger that 
\add is\add* among the children of Israel. 
\v 10 And the Levites that are gone away far from me, when Israel went astray,
