\v 26 And after he is cleansed, they shall reckon unto him seven days. 
\v 27 And in the day that he goeth into the sanctuary, unto the inner court,
to minister in the sanctuary, he shall offer his sin offering, saith the Lord
GOD. 
\v 28 And it shall be unto them for an inheritance: I \add am\add* their
inheritance: and ye shall give them no possession in Israel: I \add am
\add* their possession. 
\v 29 They shall eat the meat offering, and the sin offering, and the trespass
offering; and every dedicated thing in Israel shall be theirs. 
\v 30 And the first of all the firstfruits of all \add things,\add* and every
oblation of all, of every \add sort\add* of your oblations, shall be the
priest’s: ye shall also give unto the priest the first of your dough, that he
