\v 31 The priests shall not eat of any thing that is dead of itself, or torn,
whether it be fowl or beast.
\c 45
\p
\v 1 Moreover, when ye shall divide by lot the land for inheritance, ye shall
offer an oblation unto the LORD, an holy portion of the land: the length 
\add shall be\add* the length of five and twenty thousand \add reeds,
\add* and the breadth \add shall be\add* ten thousand. This \add shall be
\add* holy in all the borders thereof round about. 
\v 2 Of this there shall be for the sanctuary five hundred \add in length,
\add* with five hundred \add in breadth,\add* square round about; and fifty
cubits round about for the suburbs thereof. 
\v 3 And of this measure shalt thou measure the length of five and twenty
thousand, and the breadth of ten thousand: and in it shall be the sanctuary 
\add and\add* the most holy \add place. \add*
\v 4 The holy \add portion\add* of the land shall be for the priests the
ministers of the sanctuary, which shall come near to minister unto the LORD:
and it shall be a place for their houses, and an holy place for the
sanctuary. 
\v 5 And the five and twenty thousand of length, and the ten thousand of
breadth, shall also the Levites, the ministers of the house, have for
themselves, for a possession for twenty chambers.
\p
\v 6 And ye shall appoint the possession of the city five thousand broad, and
five and twenty thousand long, over against the oblation of the holy 
\add portion:\add* it shall be for the whole house of Israel.
\p
\v 7 And \add a portion shall be\add* for the prince on the one side and on
the other side of the oblation of the holy \add portion,\add* and of the
possession of the city, before the oblation of the holy \add portion,
\add* and before the possession of the city, from the west side westward, and
from the east side eastward: and the length \add shall be\add* over against
one of the portions, from the west border unto the east border. 
\v 8 In the land shall be his possession in Israel: and my princes shall no
more oppress my people; and \add the rest of\add* the land shall they give to
the house of Israel according to their tribes.
\p
\v 9 Thus saith the Lord GOD; Let it suffice you, O princes of Israel: remove
violence and spoil, and execute judgment and justice, take away your exactions
