\v 10 Ye shall have just balances, and a just ephah, and a just bath. I 
\v 11 The ephah and the bath shall be of one measure, that the bath may
contain the tenth part of an homer, and the ephah the tenth part of an homer:
the measure thereof shall be after the homer. 
\v 12 And the shekel \add shall be\add* twenty gerahs: twenty shekels, five
and twenty shekels, fifteen shekels, shall be your maneh. 
\v 13 This \add is\add* the oblation that ye shall offer; the sixth part of an
