way of the gate whereby he came in, but shall go forth over against it. 
\v 10 And the prince in the midst of them, when they go in, shall go in; and
when they go forth, shall go forth. 
\v 11 And in the feasts and in the solemnities the meat offering shall be an
ephah to a bullock, and ephah to a ram, and to the lambs as he is able to
give, and an hin of oil to an ephah. 
\v 12 Now when the prince shall prepare a voluntary burnt offering or peace
offerings voluntarily unto the LORD, \add one\add* shall then open him the
gate that looketh toward the east, and he shall prepare his burnt offering and
his peace offerings, as he did on the sabbath day: then he shall go forth; and
after his going forth \add one\add* shall shut the gate. 
\v 13 Thou shalt daily prepare a burnt offering unto the LORD \add of
\add* a lamb of the first year without blemish: thou shalt prepare it every
morning. 
\v 14 And thou shalt prepare a meat offering for it every morning, the sixth
part of an ephah, and the third part of an hin of oil, to temper with the fine
